description:
This is a 9 minute workout called 'Belly breathing exercise: Calming the body and mind' from the channel Indiana University School of Medicine.
The workout falls under Rest/Breathing exercises and Rest/Meditation.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Deep Recharge and The Sleep Prep vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Living with a chronic disease can often result in extra stress and anxiety, especially for children. In partnership with Riley Childrenâ€™s Foundation and Riley Hospital for Children, Indiana University School of Medicine clinicians and researchers are pleased to present a video resource to support patients coping with stress. By following the steps presented in the video, viewers will learn how to complete a belly breathing exercise that can be done anywhere at any time. Belly breathing is a great way to calm the body and mind....
